                    </ul>
                      <p> Another way to find an apartment in Toronto is to do some old-fashioned legwork. Toronto’s daily newspapers usually update their classified each night at around 1:00 am. Here are some daily newspapers you can check out: </p>
                      <ul>
                        <li> <a href="http://www.starclassifieds.com/marketplace/"> The Toronto Star </a> </li>
                        <li> <a href="http://classifieds.torontosun.com/"> Toronto Sun </a> </li>
                        <li> <a href="http://www.theglobeandmail.com/classifieds/"> The Globe and the Mail</a> </li>
                      </ul>
                      <p> If you are flying in from out of town, you may want to hold back from committing yourself to a residence to prevent surprises. Of course, you will then need to think about a temporary “home” while you shop around and vacancy is always a problem. If you want to commit yourself to a residence prior to your arrival here, make sure someone has looked at the place for you. </p>
